<h2>
    Styling HTML
</h2>
<p>
    Styling (colors, margin/padding, etc.) is done with Cascading Style Sheets, or 
    CSS for short. It must be linked to the main HTML document or it can 
    be inside a <code class="lang-html">&lt;style&gt;</code> tag on the same page. 
</p>
<pre><code class="lang-html">&lt;!-- Link into Style Sheet -->
&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/prism.css" asp-append-version="true" /></code></pre>
<pre><code class="lang-html">&lt;!-- Using the Style Tag -->
&lt;style&gt;
p {
    color: red;
 }
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;p &gt; Cola is great! &lt;/p&gt;</code></pre>

<p>
    There is also an attribute <code>style</code> that can be used to set 
    the styling of an element. 
</p>
<pre><code class="lang-html">&lt;!-- in-line style -->
&lt;p style="color: blueviolet;"&gt; Cola is great! &lt;/p&gt;</code></pre>

<!-- in-line style -->
<p style="color: blueviolet;"> Cola is great! </p>

<h2>
    Links
</h2>
<p>
    Hyperlinks, or links for short, or created with the anchor tag <code>&lt;a&gt;</code>
    and are common in HTML. It links one place on the internet to another and makes 
    the internet a network. 
</p>
<p>
    The URL goes inside of the <code>href</code> attribute and controls where the
